pageContext.claim: “Today there are more people working than at any time in the history of our country, so I don't think there's going to be a blue wave.”
pageContext.analysis: The United States has a record number of job openings and the unemployment rate is the lowest it has been since April 2000. If it falls any lower (and most economists say it will), Trump would be presiding over the lowest rate since 1969 (when unemployment fell to 3.5 percent). But it is not there yet.
